name: Polis House
street: Woodlawn Avenue and West Cassilly Street
directions:
First floor bathroom is near the lobby, you can get there by the wheelchair ramp outside.   
Basement restroom is down the central staircase and to the right in the small hallway.  It is small.
comment:
The first floor restroom is supposed to be for Wittenberg residents only, but no one enforces this, and it includes shower with changing area for privacy.  If you look like a college student and just knock, someone will let you in to the building.  
The basement floor restroom is supposed to be for guests, but has no shower and is tiny.
